  "texts": [
    "The error in the model, also known as the loss function, is chosen as a continuous function to enable the use of stochastic gradient descent for adjusting the parameters of the model.",
    "The commonly used loss function involves the entropy of an infinite stream of words, as defined by Shannon (1948), Cover (1999).",
    "Intuitively, entropy is the measure of information in the stream and is a lower bound on the capacity of a channel required to transmit the stream.",
    "Let l > 0 specify the sequence length.",
    "Consider a sequence of l words, s = w 1 w 2...w l-1 w l."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The commonly used loss function involves the entropy of an infinite stream of words, as defined by Shannon (1948), Cover (1999)."
  ]
}